@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Tutorial";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_AdministratorLayout.cshtml";
}

<h2>Tutorial</h2>

<h3>Check the rubric or template</h3>
<div class="well">
    <ol>In the navbar click 'All Rubrics' or click here @Html.ActionLink("All Rubrics", "AllRubrics", "Rubric")</ol>
    <ol>A page will open up with a drop down with the list of the list of departments. Select any department from the list.</ol>
    <ol>On selecting the option from the list, jquery will fetch the list of all the rubrics from the database.</ol>
    <ol>From the list, select any particular rubric and then click the 'SEARCH' button.</ol>
    <ol>A table with all the details about the selected rubric will be displayed. There are options of sending the rubric tot he Instructor or EDIT the rubric</ol>
</div>
<hr />
<h3>Send Rubric</h3>
<div class="well">
    <ol>Select SEND Button</ol>
    <ol> A list of all the Instructors present in the system will show up. Select the particular instructor and click send</ol>
    <ol>A EMAIL will be sent to the Instructor with the Link displayed on the screen.</ol>
</div>



<h3>Completing Assessment</h3>
<div class="well">
    <ol>
        On clicking the assessment link generated by the system, a reference look up rubric will show up with details about the ratings. The form will be displaying details that needs to
        be filled up by the Instructor.
    </ol>
    <ol>Instructor will complete the assessment considering individual student. For each student, the values should be properly selected. Incomplete selection of options will not update the results.</ol>
    <ol>On completion, instructor will submit the form. The data will be stored in the database and an confirmation message will be shown to the Instructor.</ol>
</div>

<h3>Assessment Data</h3>
<div class="well">
    <ol>This link @Html.ActionLink("Assessment Results", "AllData", "Results") will show the assessed data submitted by the Instructor</ol>
    <ol>The page displays the data about each course, Instructor and semester. The table is responsive and can be sorted by semester, courses, instructor's name and rubrics.</ol>
    <ol>The last column shows the percentage of performance of the overall students.</ol>
    <ol>The search box helps admin to search for particular results based on Instructor name, semester, course or performance indicator or rubric codes.</ol>
</div>

<div class="well">
    <h3>There some more features in the system like</h3>
    <ol>Adding a new rubric or click here @Html.ActionLink("New Rubric", "Create", "Rubric")</ol>
    <ol>Editing the rubric</ol>
    <ol>Deleting the rubric</ol>
    <ol>Adding new instructor or click here @Html.ActionLink("New Instructor", "Insert", "Instructor")</ol>
    <ol>Editing  on instructor</ol>
    <ol>Deleting an Instructor Record</ol>
</div>

